The fix is correct and complete. Let me summarize the issue and solution:

## Summary

**Issue**: `SharedFlow.toList(mutableList)` and `SharedFlow.toSet(mutableSet)` in version 1.7.0-Beta were ignoring the `destination` parameter. When users passed a mutable collection to accumulate results, it was completely ignored.

**Root Cause**: In `Lint.kt`, the implementations were:
```kotlin
// BEFORE (buggy)
public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toList(destination: MutableList<T> = ArrayList()): List<T> =
    (this as Flow<T>).toList()  // 'destination' parameter is ignored!

public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toSet(destination: MutableSet<T> = LinkedHashSet()): Set<T> =
    (this as Flow<T>).toSet()   // 'destination' parameter is ignored!
```

The `destination` parameter was declared but never passed to the underlying `Flow.toList()` / `Flow.toSet()` calls.

**Fix**: Pass the `destination` parameter to the underlying implementations:
```kotlin
// AFTER (fixed)
public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toList(destination: MutableList<T> = ArrayList()): List<T> =
    (this as Flow<T>).toList(destination)  // Now correctly passes destination!

public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toSet(destination: MutableSet<T> = LinkedHashSet()): Set<T> =
    (this as Flow<T>).toSet(destination)   // Now correctly passes destination!
```

Now when users use the pattern from the issue:
```kotlin
val acc = MutableList()
val job = scope.launch(start = Undispatched) {
  sharedFlow.toList(acc)  // Items are now correctly collected into 'acc'
}
job.cancel()
// acc now contains the collected items
```

The collected items will properly appear in `acc` as expected in version 1.6.4.
